00:02:17.920 --> 00:02:18.920
Yikes.

00:02:18.920 --> 00:02:19.970
He's still out there somewhere].

00:02:19.970 --> 00:02:24.000
The most isolated tribe in the world is a
tough one to guess, but there are two known

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:27.319
tribes on the Andaman Islands off the coast
of India.

00:02:27.319 --> 00:02:31.870
The most famous of the two are the Sentinelese
who were described in 1290 by Marco Polo,

00:02:31.870 --> 00:02:34.970
as "a most violent and cruel generation."

00:02:34.970 --> 00:02:36.989
They have no desire to join modern society.

00:02:36.989 --> 00:02:42.080
They've fought off National Geographic and
police helicopters with bows and arrows, and

00:02:42.080 --> 00:02:44.250
kill fisherman who land on their island.

00:02:44.250 --> 00:02:49.390
Estimates say there may be as few as 40, but
we can't get close enough to tell.

00:02:49.390 --> 00:02:53.780
The dangers to these isolated tribes are many,
and it's not just loggers with chainsaws or

00:02:53.780 --> 00:02:55.300
drug traffickers with guns.

00:02:55.300 --> 00:03:01.349
In 1980, a mission trip from Florida set up
camp in Colombia near the isolated Nukak tribe

00:03:01.349 --> 00:03:03.130
hoping to evangelize them.

00:03:03.130 --> 00:03:07.400
Since these tribes are mainly living hunter-gatherer
lifestyles the missionaries brought metal

00:03:07.400 --> 00:03:09.450
tools to gain their trust.

00:03:09.450 --> 00:03:14.099
But because of the Nukak's lack of immunity
to modern viruses and bacteria, the missionaries

00:03:14.099 --> 00:03:16.569
brought axes, machetes and disease.

00:03:16.569 --> 00:03:21.440
They were stricken with respiratory infections
and other diseases before being treated.

00:03:21.440 --> 00:03:24.819
Most of them now live in poverty in a city
near their old land.

00:03:24.819 --> 00:03:31.849
A study in Nature[a] of 238 indigenous populations
in South America found declines averaged 43-percent

00:03:31.849 --> 00:03:33.910
after contact with outsiders.

00:03:33.910 --> 00:03:38.140
Even simply contacting the tribes directly
completely changes their chosen way of life.

00:03:38.140 --> 00:03:39.819
Remember that tribe from the beginning?

00:03:39.819 --> 00:03:43.629
A month later, they'd emerged again, with
the flu.

00:03:43.629 --> 00:03:45.880
Which brings to mind a whole OTHER consideration.

00:03:45.880 --> 00:03:47.870
Should we leave these people be?

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:49.460
Or find a way to contact them?

